'''David Jurásek''' (born 7 August 2000) is a Czech professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left-back]] for [[Czech First League]] club [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]]. He also represents the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic national team]].

==Club career==

===Early career===
Jurásek began his career in the academy at Dolní Němčí, later moving to [[1. FC Slovácko|Slovácko]] and then to [[FC Zbrojovka Brno|Zbrojovka Brno]].<ref name = "MB">{{cite web|url=https://www.fkmb.cz/clanky.php?article=12168|title=Defenzivní talent Jurásek přestoupil do Boleslavi z Prostějova|date=16 July 2021|accessdate=25 February 2022|publisher=FK Mladá Boleslav|language=cs|archive-date=5 August 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230805105416/https://www.fkmb.cz/clanky.php?article=12168|url-status=dead}}</ref>

He made his professional debut for Zbrojovka Brno in a 0–0 draw against [[FK Dukla Prague|Dukla Prague]] on 1 July 2020, replacing [[Ondřej Vaněk]] as a substitute in the final minute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://fczbrno.cz/zapas.asp?ID=Spousta-sanci-zadna-branka-Zbrojovka-remizovala-s-Duklou-3470|title=Spousta šancí, žádná branka. Zbrojovka remizovala s Duklou |publisher=FC Zbrojovka Brno|accessdate=1 June 2020|language=cs}}</ref> After six [[Czech National Football League]] appearances for the club, Jurásek signed for [[1. SK Prostějov|Prostějov]] in July 2020. At Prostějov, Jurásek made 25 league appearances, scoring three times, before signing for [[Czech First League]] club [[FK Mladá Boleslav|Mladá Boleslav]] in July 2021.<ref name = "MB"/> Upon joining Mladá Boleslav, Jurásek told [[Prostějov]]-based newspaper ''Prostějovský Večerník'' that his time in the second tier with Prostějov had been instrumental in earning a move to Mladá Boleslav.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vecernikpv.cz/rozhovory/5535-david-jurasek-bez-prostejova-bych-se-do-boleslavi-vubec-nedostal-usmiva-se-po-prestupu|title=David Jurásek: "Bez Prostějova bych se do Boleslavi vůbec nedostal," usmívá se po přestupu |publisher=Prostějovský Večerník|date=3 July 2021|accessdate=25 February 2022|language=cs}}</ref> On 21 August 2021, Jurásek made his debut in the Czech First League, starting in a 3–1 win against [[FK Teplice|Teplice]].<ref>{{Soccerway|ID=616370}}</ref>

===Slavia Prague===
On 10 February 2022, following one goal and two assists in 15 league games, [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]] announced Jurásek and fellow Mladá Boleslav teammate [[Daniel Fila]] had signed for the club, with the pair both signing contracts until June 2026.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.slavia.cz/clanek.asp?id=Fila-and-Jur-225-sek-join-Slavia-963|title=Fila and Jurásek join Slavia |publisher=SK Slavia Praha|date=10 February 2022|accessdate=25 February 2022}}</ref>

===Benfica===
On 10 July 2023, Jurásek signed a five-year contract with Portuguese side [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]], in a deal totalling €14 million. His release clause was set at €80 million.<ref>{{cite web|last=Malý|first=Jan|url=https://www.sport.cz/clanek/fotbal-ceska-1-liga-jurasek-uz-patri-benfice-je-jejim-druhym-nejdrazsim-obrancem-v-historii-4326550|title=Jurásek už patří Benfice, je jejím druhým nejdražším obráncem v historii|website=[[Seznam.cz|Sport.cz]]|date=10 July 2023|accessdate=10 July 2023|language=cs}}</ref> He made his debut for the club on 9 August, in the [[Supertaça Cândido de Oliveira]] coming off the bench to replace [[Mihailo Ristić (footballer)|Mihailo Ristić]] at half-time in a 2–0 win over [[O Clássico|rivals]] [[FC Porto|Porto]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Benfica soube mudar para ganhar a Supertaça |trans-title=Benfica knew how to change to win Supercup |url=https://www.publico.pt/2023/08/09/desporto/cronica_de_jogo/benfica-vence-fc-porto-conquista-supertaca-2059795|date=9 August 2023|access-date=17 September 2023|publisher=[[Público (Portugal)|Público]]|language=pt}}</ref> Five days later, Jurásek made his first start for Benfica and [[Primeira Liga]] debut in a 3–2 loss away at Boavista. At the end of the match, he suffered an ankle injury<ref>{{Cite web|title=Benfica: Jurásek saiu lesionado|trans-title=Benfica: Jurásek came off injured|url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/jurasek-saiu-lesionado-2023082910103105714|publisher=[[A Bola]]|date=15 August 2023|access-date=18 September 2023|language=cs}}</ref> and got subsequently sidelined for a month.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Jurásek lesionou-se frente ao Boavista e já é conhecido o tempo de paragem|trans-title=Jurásek got injured against Boavista and stopping time is already known|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/benfica/noticias/jurasek-lesionou-se-frente-ao-boavista-e-ja-e-conhecido-o-tempo-de-paragem-16863665.html|publisher=[[O Jogo]]|date=15 August 2023|access-date=18 September 2023}}</ref> Jurásek made his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut on 3 October 2023, coming on as a substitute in the 79th minute of a 1–0 loss away at [[Inter Milan]], in the competition's [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League group stage|group stage]].<ref>{{Cite web|first=Mariana|last=Fernandes|title=Di María, a cara de uma equipa que gastou tudo para pagar uma fatura demasiado alta (a crónica do Inter Milão-Benfica)|trans-title=Di María, the face of a team that spent everything to pay a bill that was too high (the Inter Milan-Benfica chronicle) |url=https://observador.pt/2023/10/03/di-maria-a-cara-de-uma-equipa-que-gastou-tudo-para-pagar-uma-fatura-demasiado-alta-a-cronica-do-inter-milao-benfica/|date=3 October 2023|website=Observador|language=pt}}</ref>

====Hoffenheim (loan)====
On 22 January 2024, Benfica sent Jurásek on loan to [[Bundesliga]] club [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|TSG Hoffenheim]] until the end of the [[2023–24 TSG 1899 Hoffenheim season|season]], with an optional buy-clause reported to be €11 million, which could rise to €12 million with add-ons.<ref>{{Cite web|title=David Jurásek wechselt auf Leihbasis zur TSG |trans-title=David Jurásek is moving to TSG on loan |url=https://www.tsg-hoffenheim.de/aktuelles/news/2024/01/david-jurasek-wechselt-auf-leihbasis-zur-tsg/|date=24 August 2023|access-date=22 January 2024|publisher=TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|language=de}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Jurásek out on loan|url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/en-us/agora/noticias/2024/01/22/futebol-benfica-jurasek-emprestimo-hoffenheim|publisher=Benfica|date=22 January 2024}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=Mercado Benfica (oficial): Jurásek emprestado ao Hoffenheim|trans-title=Benfica Market (official): Jurásek loaned to Hoffenheim|url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/mercado-benfica-oficial-jurasek-emprestado-ao-hoffenheim-2024012209082785869|work=[[A Bola]]|date=22 January 2024|language=pt}}</ref> Later that year, on 1 July, he extended his loan contract for another year.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tsg-hoffenheim.de/aktuelles/news/2024/07/leihe-verlaengert-jurasek-bleibt-ein-weiteres-jahr-bei-der-tsg |title=Leihe verlängert – Jurásek bleibt ein weiteres Jahr bei der TSG |publisher=TSG 1899 Hoffenheim |language=de |date=1 July 2024 }}</ref>

====Beşiktaş (loan)====

On 29 June 2025, Jurásek was loaned to Turkish side [[Beşiktaş J.K.|Beşiktaş]] until the end of the season with an option to purchase clause.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bjk.com.tr/tr/haber/91916/besiktasimiza-hos-geldin-david-jurasek.html|title=Beşiktaşımıza Hoş Geldin David Jurasek|trans-title=Welcome to Beşiktaş David Jurasek|publisher=bjk.com.tr|language=tr|date=29 June 2025|access-date=29 June 2025}}</ref> However, in January 2026, having made 17 appearances for the [[Istanbul]]-based club, his loan was terminated.<ref>{{Cite web |date=12 January 2026 |title=Besiktas terminated David Jurasek's contract. |url=https://en.haberler.com/besiktas-terminated-david-jurasek-s-contract-2193812/?utm_source=facebook&utm_campaign=tavsiye_et |access-date=12 January 2026 |website=Haberler |language=}}</ref>

=== Return to Slavia Prague ===
On 12 January 2026, Jurásek permanently left Benfica, returning to Slavia Prague, where he signed a contract until June 2029, for a reported fee of €3 million.<ref>{{Cite web |date=12 January 2026 |title=Velký návrat. Slavii posílí David Jurásek |trans-title=A great comeback. Slavia will be strengthened by David Jurásek |url=https://www.slavia.cz/article/23773-Velky-navrat-Slavii-posili-David-Jurasek |access-date=12 January 2026 |publisher=[[SK Slavia Prague]] |language=Czech}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=12 January 2026 |title=Jurásek transferido |trans-title=Jurásek transferred |url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/pt-pt/agora/noticias/2026/01/12/futebol-benfica-jurasek-transferencia-definitiva-slavia-praga |access-date=12 January 2026 |publisher=[[S.L. Benfica]] |language=pt}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=12 January 2026 |title=Benfica transfere Jurásek para o Slavia de Praga por três milhões de euros |trans-title=Benfica transfers Jurásek to Slavia Prague for three million euros |url=https://www.publico.pt/2026/01/12/desporto/noticia/benfica-transfere-jurasek-slavia-praga-tres-milhoes-euros-2160944 |access-date=12 January 2026 |website=Público |language=pt}}</ref>

==International career==
On 4 April 2017, Jurásek made his debut for the [[Czech Republic national under-17 football team|Czech Republic's under-17]] side, playing in a 4–1 win against [[Belgium national under-17 football team|Belgium]]. Four years later, he earned his second youth cap for the Czech Republic, representing the [[Czech Republic national under-21 football team|under-21 team]] in a 3–0 victory against [[Kosovo national under-21 football team|Kosovo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://repre.fotbal.cz/hrac/hraci/16332705|title=David Jurásek|publisher=Football Association of the Czech Republic|access-date=25 February 2022|language=cs}}</ref>

On 24 March 2023, Jurásek debuted for the Czech senior team in [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying]] match against [[Poland national football team|Poland]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Třetí nejlepší výkon pod Šilhavým, soudí čtenáři. Exceloval debutant Jurásek|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/euro-2024/euro-2024-kvalifikace-cesko-polsko-znamkovani-ctenaru.A230325_143005_euro-2024_duff|website=[[Mladá fronta Dnes]]|publisher=[[Mafra (company)|Mafra]]|date=25 March 2023|language=cs}}</ref> He scored his first goal in a preparatory [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly match]] against [[Malta national football team|Malta]] on 8 June 2024, which ended in a 7–1 victory for the Czechs.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Tomáš|last=Myšák|title=První gól za reprezentaci? Piloval jsem to se snoubenkou, řekl Jurásek po zápase s Maltou. Co ho v nominaci překvapilo?|trans-title=First goal for the national team? "I worked it out with my fiancee", Jurásek said after the match with Malta. What surprised him in the national team?|url=https://www.ruik.cz/prvni-gol-za-reprezentaci-piloval-jsem-to-se-snoubenkou-rekl-jurasek-po-zapase-s-maltou-co-ho-v-nominaci-prekvapilo/|website=Ruik.cz|date=8 June 2024|language=cs}}</ref>

On 28 May 2024, he was selected in the 26-man squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=28 May 2024 |title=Nominace reprezentace na přípravný kemp před EURO 2024 |trans-title=National team nominations for the preparatory camp before EURO 2024 |url=https://www.fotbal.cz/repre/nominace/nominace/836 |language=cs |publisher=Czech Football Association |access-date=28 May 2024}}</ref>

